HEADWORD: Pawnees
<hw>Paw`nees"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>; <sing>sing.
<singw>Pawnee</singw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</sing> <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>A
tribe of Indians (called also <altname>Loups</altname>) who formerly
occupied the region of the Platte river, but now (1890) live mostly in
the Indian Territory (Oklahoma). The term is often used in a wider sense
to include also the related tribes of Rickarees and Wichitas. Called
also <altname>Pani</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

